summary: To the swifties that never met Taylor:
body:
To the swifties that never met Taylor:

I always see these posts about “I will never meet Taylor because I am not populair and I’m not as funny as most of you”. Well drop that bullshit right away.

I had 60 fucking followers on Tumblr when Taylor invited me to the secret sessions. And somehow she still found me and imvited me.

It’s not about being populair and having a big account. If you show your support in your posts even by only reblogging things, Taylor will see it one day and she will appreciate you for it and will invite you one day. She has too many fans to invite and notice you all. But one day it will happen. Believe me.

But stop letting yourselves down by posting these kinds of things! It will make the feeling worse. You ALL dezerve it and you ALL will get a chance one day. Just give it time and be patient!

summary:
I realize this fandom doesn't like how much attention Taylor gives All Too Well and I understand that feeling
But y'all need to...
body:
I realize this fandom doesn’t like how much attention Taylor gives All Too Well and I understand that feeling

But y'all need to remember, Taylor wrote All Too Well when she was heartbroken and we took this sadness and turned it into a collage of happy memories of us screaming the words of this songs, and us showing Taylor how much this song means to us.

Everytime I listen to All Too Well I remember this

The saddest moment in life can bring you the happiest memories.
